In 2001, Nelson Mandela joined the people of London in Trafalgar Square to celebrate the 7th anniversary of free elections in South Africa. Mandela, along with R.E.M, The Corrs, Ladysmith Black Mambazo, Dave Stewart, Hugh Masekela and Baaba Maal, took part in an unforgettable night. This television special, directed and produced by Tony Gregory, has now been re-mastered for a 2013 release, 
with net profits going to The Nelson Mandela Children's Fund and The Prince's Trust.

Mandela returns to Trafalgar Square after 40 years:
